obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (43334)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00046_189006_1523274192012&sectionId=43334&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00046_189006_1523274192012
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Charitable Endowments`
  line `Act, 1890.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India, ^1***, ^2***; and`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on the first day of October, 1890.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth Schedule`
  line `(w.e.f. 31-10- 2019).`
  line
  line `2. The words "inclusive of British Baluchistan" omitted by the A.O. 1948.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (43335)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definition.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00046_189006_1523274192012&sectionId=43335&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00046_189006_1523274192012
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act “charitable purpose” includes relief of the poor, education, medical`
  line `relief and the advancement of any other object of general public utility, but does not include a purpose`
  line `which relates exclusively to religious teaching or worship.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (43336)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Appointment and incorporation of treasurer of Charitable Endowments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00046_189006_1523274192012&sectionId=43336&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00046_189006_1523274192012
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) The`
  line `Central Government may appoint an officer of the Government by the name of his office to be`
  line `treasurer of Charitable Endowments for India, and the Government of any State may appoint an`
  line `officer of the Government by the name of his office to be treasurer of Charitable Endowments for the`
  line State].
  line
  line `(2) Such treasurer shall, for the purposes of taking, holding and transferring movable or`
  line `immovable property under the authority of this Act, be a corporation sole by the name of the treasurer`
  line `of Charitable Endowments for ^2[India or, as the case may be, the State], and, as such treasurer, shall`
  line `have perpetual succession and a corporate seal, and may sue and be sued in his corporate name.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for Sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. ibid., for "the territories subject to the L.G".`
obj_root_law_sections_3_a:
  sectionId (43337)
  sectionNo 3A
  orderNo 4
  title `Definition of “appropriate Government”, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. ibid`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00046_189006_1523274192012&sectionId=43337&sectionno=3A&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00046_189006_1523274192012
obj_root_law_sections_3_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[3A. Definition of "appropriate Government", etc.--In the subsequent provisions of this Act`
  line `the appropriate Government means, as respects a charitable endowment, the objects of which do not`
  line `extend beyond a single State and are not objects to which the executive authority of the Central`
  line `Government extends, the Government of the State, and as respects any other charitable endowment`
  line `the Central Government].`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (43338)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 5
  title `Orders vesting property in treasurer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00046_189006_1523274192012&sectionId=43338&sectionno=4&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00046_189006_1523274192012
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any property is held or is to be applied in`
  line `trust for charitable purpose, the ^1[appropriate Government], if it thinks fit, may, on application made`
  line `as hereinafter mentioned, and subject to the other provisions of this section, order, by ^2`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, that the property be vested in the treasurer of Charitable`
  line `Endowments on such terms as to the application of the property or the income thereof as may be`
  line `agreed on between the ^1[appropriate Government] and the person or persons making the application,`
  line `and the property shall thereupon so vest accordingly.`
  line
  line `(2) When any property has vested under this section in a treasurer of Charitable Endowments, he is`
  line `entitled to all documents of title relating thereto.`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
  line
  line `(4) An order under this section vesting property in a treasurer of Charitable Endowments shall not`
  line `require or be deemed to require him to administer the property, or impose or be deemed to impose`
  line `upon him the duty of a trustee with respect to the administration thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "L.G"..`
  line `2. For notifications issued under this section conjunction with s. 5, see different local R. and O.`
  line `3. Subs-section (3) omitted, ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (43339)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 6
  title `Schemes for administration of property vested in the treasurer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00046_189006_1523274192012&sectionId=43339&sectionno=5&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00046_189006_1523274192012
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) On application made`
  line `as hereinafter mentioned, and with the concurrence of the person or persons making the application,`
  line `the ^1[appropriate Government] if it thinks fit, may settle a scheme for the administration of any`
  line `property which has been or is to be vested in the treasurer of Charitable Endowments, and may in`
  line `such scheme appoint, by name or office, a person or persons, not being or including such treasurer,`
  line `toad minister the property.`
  line
  line `(2) On application made as hereinafter mentioned, and with the concurrence of the person or`
  line `persons making the application, the ^1[appropriate Government] may, if it thinks fit, modify any`
  line `scheme settled under this section or substitute another scheme in its stead.`
  line
  line `(3) A scheme settled, modified or substituted under this section shall, subject to the other`
  line `provisions of this section come into operation on a day to be appointed by the ^1[appropriate Government] in this behalf, and shall remain in force so long as the property to which it relates`
  line `continues to be vested in the treasurer of Charitable Endowments or until it has been modified or`
  line `another such scheme has been substituted in its stead.`
  line
  line `(4) Such a scheme, when it comes into operation, shall supersede any decree or direction relating`
  line `to the subject-matter thereof insofar as such decree or direction is in any way repugnant thereto, and`
  line `its validity shall not be questioned in any court, nor shall any court give, in contravention of the`
  line `provisions of the scheme or in any way contrary or in addition thereto, a decree or direction regarding`
  line `the administration of the property to which the scheme relates:`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall be construed as precluding a court from inquiring`
  line `whether the Government by which a scheme was made was the appropriate Government].`
  line
  line `(5) In the settlement of such a scheme effect shall be given to the wishes of the author of the trust`
  line `so far as they can be ascertained, and, in the opinion of the ^1[appropriate Government], effect can`
  line `reasonably be given to them.`
  line
  line `(6) Where a scheme has been settled under this section for the administration of property not`
  line `already vested in the treasurer of Charitable Endowments, it shall not come into operation until the`
  line `property has become so vested.^3`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for L.G..`
  line `2. Ins., ibid.`
  line `3. A proviso to section 5, applicable only to Bengal, has been added by the Bengal Wakf Act, 1934 (Ben. 13 of 1934),`
  line `section 79.`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (43340)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 7
  title `Mode of applying for vesting orders and schemes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes `1. A new sub-section (3), applicable only to Bengal, has been added by the Bengal Wakf Act, 1934 (Ben. 13 of 1934), s. 80.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00046_189006_1523274192012&sectionId=43340&sectionno=6&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00046_189006_1523274192012
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The application referred to in the`
  line `two last foregoing sections must be made,--`
  line
  line `(a) If the property is already held in trust for a charitable purpose, then by the person acting in`
  line `the administration of the trust, or, where there are more persons than one so acting, then by those`
  line `persons or a majority of them; and`
  line
  line `(b) If the property is to be applied in trust for such a purpose then by the person or persons`
  line `proposing so to apply it.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of this section the executor or administrator of a deceased trustee of property`
  line `held in trust for a charitable purpose shall be deemed to be a person acting in the administration of the`
  line trust.^1
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh.--`
  line
  line `Addition of section 6-A in Act II of 1890.--After section 6 of the Charitable Endowments Act,`
  line `1890, the following shall be inserted as section 6-A.`
  line
  line `"6-A. (1) If the State Government is satisfied upon representation made or otherwise, that in any`
  line `case, where any property has already vested in the Treasurer of Charitable Endowments under section`
  line `4 and a scheme has been settled under section 5 that the person or persons acting in the administration`
  line `thereof are wasting or mal-administering the same, it may by notice require the person or persons to`
  line `show cause why the scheme settled for administration be not modified or substituted by another`
  line scheme.
  line
  line `(2) The notice under sub-section (1) shall be served in such manner as may be specified.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the person or persons served with the notice fail to show cause within the time allowed`
  line `or the Government is satisfied after considering their explanation, if any, and making such enquiry as`
  line `it may deem necessary that the property is being wasted or mal-administered it may notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in section 5 or 6, modify the scheme or substitute another scheme in its place.dbtqts`
  line
  line `[Vide the Uttar Pradesh Act 37 of 1952, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (43341)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 8
  title [Omitted.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00046_189006_1523274192012&sectionId=43341&sectionno=7&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00046_189006_1523274192012
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `[Exercise by Governor General in Council of Powers of Local Government]. --Omitted by the`
  line `A.O. 1937.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (43342)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 9
  title `Bare trusteeship of treasurer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00046_189006_1523274192012&sectionId=43342&sectionno=8&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00046_189006_1523274192012
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, a treasurer of`
  line `Charitable Endowments shall not, as such treasurer, act in the administration of any trust whereof any`
  line `of the property is for the time being vested in him under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Such treasurer shall keep a separate account of each property for the time being so vested`
  line `insofar as the property consists of securities for money, and shall apply the property or the income`
  line `thereof in accordance with the provision made in that behalf in the vesting order under section 4 or in`
  line `the scheme, if any, under section 5, or in both those documents.`
  line
  line `(3) In the case of any property so vested other than securities for money, such treasurer shall,`
  line `subject to any special order which he may receive from the authority by whose order the property`
  line `became vested in him, permit the persons acting in the administration of the trust to have the`
  line `possession, management and control of the property and the application of the income thereof, as if`
  line `the property had been vested in them.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (43343)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 10
  title `Annual publication of list of properties vested in treasurer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Local Government".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00046_189006_1523274192012&sectionId=43343&sectionno=9&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00046_189006_1523274192012
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `A treasurer of Charitable`
  line `Endowments shall cause to be published annually in the Official Gazette, at such time as`
  line `the ^1[appropriate Government] may direct, a list of all properties for the time being vested in him`
  line `under this Act and an abstract of all accounts kept by him under section 2 of the last foregoing`
  line section.
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (43344)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 11
  title `Limitation of functions and powers of treasurer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00046_189006_1523274192012&sectionId=43344&sectionno=10&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00046_189006_1523274192012
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) A treasurer of Charitable`
  line `Endowments shall always be a sole trustee, and shall not, as such treasurer, take or hold any property`
  line `otherwise than under the provisions of this Act, or, subject to those provisions, transfer any property`
  line `vested in him except in obedience to a decree divesting him of the property, or in compliance with a`
  line `direction in that behalf issuing from the authority by whose order the property became vested in him.`
  line
  line `(2) Such a direction may require the treasurer to sell or otherwise dispose of any property vested in`
  line `him, and, with the sanction of the authority issuing the direction, to invest the proceeds of the sale or`
  line `other disposal of the property in any such security for money as is ^1[specified in the direction], or in`
  line `the purchase of immovable property.`
  line
  line `(3) When a treasurer of Charitable Endowments is divested, by a direction of ^2[the appropriate`
  line `Government] under this section, of any property, it shall vest in the person or persons acting in the`
  line `administration thereof and be held by him or them on the same trusts as those on which it was held by`
  line `such treasurer.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. ibid., for mentioned in section 4, sub-section (3), clause (a), (b), (c), (d), or (e).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. ibid., for "the Local Government or the Governor General in Council".`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (43345)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 12
  title `Provision for continuance of office of treasurer in certain contingencies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Local Government".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00046_189006_1523274192012&sectionId=43345&sectionno=11&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00046_189006_1523274192012
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `If the office`
  line `held by an officer of the Government who has been appointed to be treasurer of Charitable`
  line `Endowments is abolished or its name is changed, the ^1[appropriate Government] may appoint the`
  line `same or another office of the Government by the name of his office to be such treasurer, and`
  line `thereupon the holder of the latter office shall be deemed for the purposes of this Act to be the`
  line `successor in office of the holder of the former office.`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (43346)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 13
  title `Transfer of property from one treasurer to another.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. ibid., for section 12.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00046_189006_1523274192012&sectionId=43346&sectionno=12&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00046_189006_1523274192012
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `^1[Transfer of property from one treasurer to another--If by reason of any alteration of`
  line `areas or by reason of the appointment of a treasurer of Charitable Endowments for India or for any`
  line `State for which such a treasurer has not previously been appointed or for any other reason it appears`
  line `to the Central Government that any property vested in a treasurer of Charitable Endowments should`
  line `be vested in another such treasurer, that Government may direct that the property shall be so vested`
  line `and thereupon it shall vest in that other treasurer and his successors as fully and effectually for the`
  line `purposes of this Act as if it had been originally vested in him under this Act].`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Karnataka
  line
  line `Insertion of new section 12A.--After section 12 of the Charitable Endowments Act, 1890`
  line `(Central Act 6 of 1890), as in force in the [State of Karnataka], the following section shall be inserted,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `"12A. Delegation of powers.--Where the appropriate Government is the State Government, it`
  line `may by notification in the official Gazette, direct that any power exercisable by it under this Act`
  line `(except the power to make rules under section 13) or rules made thereunder shall, in respect of any`
  line `endowment which does not exceed rupees ten thousand in value, in relation to such matters and`
  line `subject to such conditions, if any, as may be specified in the direction, be exercisable also by such`
  line `officer or authority subordinate to the State Government as may be specified in the notification:`
  line
  line `Provided that the powers under sections 4 and 5 shall not be delegated to any officer other than`
  line `the Head of a Department of Government."`
  line
  line `[Vide Karnataka Act 19 of 1973, s. 2].`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (43347)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 14
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00046_189006_1523274192012&sectionId=43347&sectionno=13&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00046_189006_1523274192012
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `^1[Power to make rules.--,^2[(1)] The ^3[appropriate Government] may ^4[, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette], make rules consistent with this Act for`
  line
  line `(a) prescribing the fees to be paid to the Government in respect of any property vested under`
  line `this Act in a treasurer of Charitable Endowments;`
  line
  line `(b) regulating the cases and the mode in which schemes or any modification thereof are to be`
  line `published before they are settled or made under section 5;`
  line
  line `(c) prescribing the forms in which accounts are to be kept by treasurers of Charitable`
  line `Endowments and the mode in which such accounts are to be audited; and`
  line
  line `(d) generally carrying into effect the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `^4[(2) Every rule made by the State Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after`
  line `it is made, before the State Legislature.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be`
  line `after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days`
  line `which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the`
  line `expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both`
  line `Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the Rule should not be`
  line `made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case`
  line `may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the`
  line `validity of anything previously done under that rule.]`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 38 of 1920, s. 2 and the First Schedule, Pt. I, for section 13.`
  line `2. Sub-section (2) of section 13 re-numbered as sub-section (1) by Act 56 of 1982, s. 2. Earlier sub-section (1) omitted by the`
  line `A. O. 1937.`
  line `3 Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Local Government".`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 56 of 1982, s. 2.`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (43348)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 15
  title `Indemnity to Government and treasurer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00046_189006_1523274192012&sectionId=43348&sectionno=14&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00046_189006_1523274192012
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `No suit shall be instituted against the`
  line `Government in respect of anything done or purporting to be done under this Act, or in respect of any`
  line `alleged neglect or omission to perform any duty devolving on the Government under this Act, or in`
  line `respect of the exercise of, or the failure to exercise, any power conferred by this Act on the`
  line `Government, nor shall any suit be instituted against a treasurer of Charitable Endowments except for`
  line `divesting him of property on the ground of its not being subject to a trust for a charitable purpose, or for making him chargeable with or accountable for the loss or misapplication of any property vested`
  line `in him, or the income thereof, where the loss or misapplication has been occasioned by or through his`
  line `willful neglect or default.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (43349)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 16
  title `Saving with respect to Advocate General and Official Trustee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00046_189006_1523274192012&sectionId=43349&sectionno=15&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00046_189006_1523274192012
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Act shall`
  line `be construed to impair the operation ^1[of any enactment] for the time being in force, respecting the`
  line `authority of an Advocate General ^2*** to act with respect to any charity ^3[or of the Official Trustees`
  line `Act, 1913] respecting the vesting of property in trust for a charitable purpose in an Official Trustee.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 58 of 1960, s. 3 and the Second Schedule, for of section III of the Statue 53, George III, Chapter 155, or of`
  line `any other enactment.`
  line `2. The words at a Presidency omitted by s. 3 and the Second Schedule, ibid.`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 3 and the Second Schedule, ibid., for or of sections 8, 9, 10, and 11 of Act No. XVII of 1864 (An Act to`
  line `constitute an office of Official Trustee).`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
